text.tspan: <distro> is no longer supported. This means that it will no longer receive security updates. It is recommended that you
upgrade to a more recent version.

flowRoot.flowPara: End of life infobar can be shown both when there are updates available (such as application updates, or updates from PPAs/COPRs) and when there aren't. When there aren't updates, a more negative icon and label are used than the standard "up to date", in order to avoid giving contradictory messages.
If there are updates that have been downloaded, and a check is being run, the existing updates are insensitive. This communicates that the existing updates are still around but can't be used.
